{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A file placed inside a subdirectory of the watched root is processed, not only files placed directly in the root directory.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Real failure boundary is OS filesystem event behavior for nested paths (REAL-INFRA, MOCK-HIDE). Many watcher backends differ on recursive semantics, so mocked/in-process events can miss this. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because behavior is pure filesystem watching with no model decision.","test_description":"Start the real daemon against a temp watched root on the host OS. Create a nested subdirectory and write a file inside it. Assert one transformation output appears in the output directory for that nested file without restarting the daemon.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The deduplication logic correctly discards a second processing request for the same file path within a configurable time window.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is at module handoff (request intake -> dedup state -> pipeline trigger), not OS-specific by itself (MOCK-MISS). In-process wiring with fake clock/time control can catch real bug. Rejected System because behavior text is about duplicate requests by path/time window, not real OS watcher semantics. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because no AI/ML output dependency.","test_description":"Wire daemon request-ingest + dedup + processing modules in-process with a controllable clock. Submit two processing requests for the same path within the configured window. Assert only one processing execution occurs and second request is dropped.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When the operating system emits multiple filesystem events for a single file write, the daemon processes the file exactly once.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly depends on OS emitting duplicate events (REAL-INFRA). Mocked watcher events can hide backend-specific burst patterns (MOCK-HIDE). Rejected Agentic/Workflow because no model output is involved.","test_description":"Run daemon with real filesystem watcher. Perform a single write pattern known to generate multiple events (e.g., temp-write + rename or multi-chunk write) and capture process invocations. Assert exactly one processing result/output for that file.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.9,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"If the watched directory is removed and then recreated while the daemon is running, the daemon resumes watching the new directory without a restart.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is OS/inode/watch-handle lifecycle behavior (REAL-INFRA) and commonly fails only with real watcher backends after delete/recreate. In-process fakes usually do not model handle invalidation accurately (MOCK-HIDE). Rejected Agentic/Workflow because no AI/ML component.","test_description":"Launch daemon watching a real temp directory. Delete the watched directory, recreate it at the same path, then add a new file. Assert daemon continues running and processes the post-recreate file without restart.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.95,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When multiple files arrive at the same time, they are processed in the order determined by their creation timestamps.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Ordering depends on real file metadata/timestamp granularity plus concurrent arrival event timing, which are OS/filesystem behaviors (REAL-INFRA). Mocked arrivals can hide races and timestamp-resolution edge cases (MOCK-HIDE). Rejected Agentic/Workflow because ordering rule has no model decision.","test_description":"Start daemon on a real watched directory. Create multiple files nearly simultaneously with controlled creation times (or staged writes with known timestamp deltas). Record processing order and assert it matches creation-timestamp order.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"A file that is still being written to when the arrival event fires is not picked up for processing until writing is complete.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Requires real partial-write timing and real watcher event timing; in-process fakes often cannot reproduce write-in-progress race accurately (REAL-INFRA, MOCK-HIDE). Rejected Agentic/Workflow because no AI/ML output dependency.","test_description":"Run daemon with real watcher. Begin writing a large file in chunks with pauses so arrival event can fire mid-write. Assert processing does not start on partial content and only starts after writer closes/completes the file.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.95,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
